/dev/ -> directory for device MGMT
sda -> block devices
lsblk -> lists disks and partitions
df -h -> same thing

fdisk /dev/DISK_NAME

n -> To Create A New Partition
p -> Primary Partition
Last Sector-> +4G -> Here You define the Size of Partition
w -> write and exit

sudo apt install xfsprogs

mkfs.xfs /dev/Partition -> Formats A Partition into Specific Format

mount /dev/Partition Mount_Point -> Selects MountPoint For A Partition
